#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Minimal requirements for public mirrors"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:11
msgid ""
"We always welcome new public mirrors. But they should be well maintained and "
"hosted in a 24/7 data center like environment. Available bandwidth should be "
"at least 1 GBit/s. We prefer mirrors offering dual-stack (IPv4 & IPv6). "
"Please do not submit mirrors configured using dynamic DNS. If you are "
"offering a mirror in a region that has only few mirrors, we will also accept "
"slower speeds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:13
msgid ""
"Please do not submit mirrors which are hosted in a Anycast-CDN like "
"Cloudflare, etc. as this can lead to sub-optimal performance with the "
"selection of fastest mirror in `dnf`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:15
msgid ""
"Please note that we are not allowed to accept public mirrors in countries "
"subject to US export regulations. You can find a list of those countries "
"here: [https://www.bis.doc.gov/index.php/policy-guidance/country-guidance/"
"sanctioned-destinations](https://www.bis.doc.gov/index.php/policy-guidance/"
"country-guidance/sanctioned-destinations)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:17
msgid ""
"As of this writing (late 2022), storage space requirements for mirroring all "
"current and past Rocky Linux releases is about 2 TB."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:20
msgid ""
"Our master mirror is `rsync://msync.rockylinux.org/rocky/mirror/pub/rocky/` "
"For your first synchronization use a mirror near to you. You can find all "
"official mirrors here: https://mirrors.rockylinux.org"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:22
msgid ""
"Please note that we might restrict access to the official master mirror to "
"official public mirrors in the future. So please consider `rsyncing` from a "
"public mirror close to you if you are running a private mirror. Also local "
"mirrors might be faster to sync from."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up your mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:26
msgid ""
"Please set up a cron job to synchronize your mirror periodically and let it "
"run around 6 times a day. But be sure to sync off the hour to help "
"distribute the load over time. If you only check against changes of "
"`fullfiletimelist-rocky` and only do a full sync if this file has changed "
"you can synchronize every hour."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:28
msgid "Here are some crontab examples for you:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#This will synchronize your mirror at 0:50, 4:50, 8:50, 12:50, 16:50, 20:50\n"
"50 */6  * * * /path/to/your/rocky-rsync-mirror.sh > /dev/null 2>&1\n"
"\n"
"#This will synchronize your mirror at 2:25, 6:25, 10:25, 14:25, 18:25, 22:25\n"
"25 2,6,10,14,18,22 * * * /path/to/your/rocky-rsync-mirror.sh > /dev/null 2>&1\n"
"\n"
"#This will synchronize your mirror every hour at 15 minutes past the hour.\n"
"#Only use if you are using our example script\n"
"15 * * * * /path/to/your/rocky-rsync-mirror.sh > /dev/null 2>&1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:42
msgid "For a simple synchronization you can use the following `rsync` command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "rsync -aqH --delete source-mirror destination-dir\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:47
msgid ""
"Consider using a locking mechanism to avoid running more than one `rsync` "
"job simultaneously when we push a new release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:49
msgid ""
"You can also use and modify our example script implementing locking and full "
"sync if required. It can be found at [https://github.com/rocky-linux/rocky-"
"tools/blob/main/mirror/mirrorsync.sh](https://github.com/rocky-linux/rocky-"
"tools/blob/main/mirror/mirrorsync.sh)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:51
msgid ""
"After your first complete synchronization check that everything is fine with "
"your mirror. Most importantly check all files and dirs got synchronized, "
"your cron job is working properly and your mirror is reachable from the "
"public Internet. Double check your firewall rules! To avoid any problems do "
"not enforce http to https redirection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:53
msgid ""
"If you have any questions setting up your mirror join https://chat."
"rockylinux.org/rocky-linux/channels/infrastructure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:55
msgid ""
"When you are done head over to the next section and propose your mirror to "
"become public!"
msgstr ""

