#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:62
msgid "Rocky uses Fedora's Mirror Manager for organizing community mirrors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:64
msgid ""
"Access Rocky's Mirror Manager here: https://mirrors.rockylinux.org/"
"mirrormanager/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:66
msgid ""
"After a successful login, your profile will be on the top right. Select the "
"drop down then click \"My sites\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:68
msgid ""
"A new page will load listing all of the sites under the account. The first "
"time it will be empty. Click \"Register a new site\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:70
msgid ""
"A new page will load with an important Export Compliance statement to read. "
"Then fill out the following information:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:78
msgid "\"Site Name\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:78
msgid ""
"\"Site Password\" - used by `report_mirrors` script, you make this anything "
"you want"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:78
msgid ""
"\"Organization URL\" - Company/School/Organization URL e.g. https://"
"rockylinux.org/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:78
msgid "\"Private\" - Checking this box hides your mirror from public use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:78
msgid ""
"\"User active\" - Uncheck this box to temporarily disable this site, it will "
"be removed from public listings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:78
msgid ""
"\"All sites can pull from me?\" - Enable all mirror sites to pull from me "
"without explicitly adding them to my list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:78
msgid ""
"\"Comments for downstream siteadmins. Please include your synchronization "
"source here to avoid dependency loops.\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:80
msgid "Upon clicking \"Submit\" you will be returned to the main mirror page."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring the site"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:84
msgid ""
"From the main mirror page, select the drop down then click \"My sites\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:86
msgid ""
"The account site page will load and the site should be listed. Click on it "
"to go to the Information Site."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:88
msgid ""
"All of the options from the last section are listed again. At the bottom of "
"the page are three new options: Admins, Hosts, and Delete site. Click on the "
"\"Hosts [add]\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create new host"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:92
msgid "Fill out the following options that are appropriate for the site:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid "\"Host name\" - required: FQDN of server as seen by a public end user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"User active\" - Uncheck this box to temporarily disable this host, it will "
"be removed from public listings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid "\"Country\" - required: 2-letter ISO country code"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"Bandwidth\" - required: integer megabits/sec, how much bandwidth this host "
"can serve"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"Private\" - e.g. not available to the public, an internal private mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid "\"Internet2\" - on Internet2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid "\"Internet2 clients\" - serves Internet2 clients, even if private"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"ASN - Autonomous System Number, used in BGP routing tables. Only if you "
"are an ISP."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"ASN Clients? - Serve all clients from the same ASN. Used for ISPs, "
"companies, or schools, not personal networks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"Robot email\" - email address, will receive notice of upstream content "
"updates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"Comment\" - text, anything else you'd like a public end user to know about "
"your mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"\"Max connections\" - Maximum parallel download connections per client, "
"suggested via metalinks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:107
msgid ""
"Click \"Create\" and it will redirect back to the Information site for the "
"host."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "Update host"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:111
msgid ""
"At the bottom of the Information site, the option for \"Hosts\" should now "
"display the host title next to it. Click on the name to load the host page. "
"All of the same options from the previous step are listed again. There are "
"new options at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:113
msgid ""
"\"Site-local Netblocks\": Netblocks are used to try to guide and end user to "
"a site-specific mirror. For example, a university might list their "
"netblocks, and the mirrorlist CGI would return the university-local mirror "
"rather than a country-local mirror. Format is one of 18.0.0.0/255.0.0.0, "
"18.0.0.0/8, an IPv6 prefix/length, or a DNS hostname. Values must be public "
"IP addresses (no RFC1918 private space addresses). Use only if you are an "
"ISP and/or own a publicly routeable netblock!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:115
msgid ""
"\"Peer ASNs\": Peer ASNs are used to guide an end user on nearby networks to "
"our mirror. For example, a university might list their peer ASNs, and the "
"mirrorlist CGI would return the university-local mirror rather than a "
"country-local mirror. You must be in the MirrorManager administrators group "
"in order to create new entries here."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:117
msgid ""
"\"Countries Allowed\": Some mirrors need to restrict themselves to serving "
"only end users from their country. If you're one of these, list the 2-letter "
"ISO code for the countries you will allow end users to be from. The "
"mirrorlist CGI will honor this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:119
msgid ""
"\"Categories Carried\": Hosts carry categories of software. Example Fedora "
"categories include Fedora and Fedora Archive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:121
msgid "Click on the \"[add]\" link under \"Categories Carried\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:122
#, no-wrap
msgid "Categories Carried"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:125
msgid ""
"For the Category, select \"Rocky Linux\" then \"Create\" to load the URL "
"page. Then click \"[add]\" to load the \"Add host category URL\" page. There "
"is one option. Repeat as needed for each of the mirrors supported protocols."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:127
msgid "\"URL\" - URL (rsync, https, http) pointing to the top directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:132
msgid ""
"Examples: * `http://rocky.example.com` * `https://rocky.example.com` * "
"`rsync://rocky.example.com`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wrap up"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/mirror_management/add_mirror_manager.md:136
msgid ""
"Once the information is filled out, the site should appear on the mirror "
"list as soon as the next mirror refresh occurs."
msgstr ""
